#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/india.rst:649
msgid ":abbr:`TDS (tax deducted at source)` and :abbr:`TCS (tax collected at source)` are tax provisions under Indian law, triggered when transaction amounts exceed specified thresholds. This alert notifies users when the value of invoices or bills surpasses these limits, prompting the application of the appropriate TDS/TCS."
